headline: Biggest Gains in Customer Satisfaction in the Management Top 250
summary: Carnival’s score for customer satisfaction increased more from a year earlier than that of any other company in the latest Management Top 250.  Companies are graded in five categories: customer satisfaction, innovation, social responsibility, employee engagement and development, and financial strength.  The statistical model that produces the ranking was created by researchers at Claremont Graduate University’s Drucker Institute.
